{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c8794b23-f0b7-4293-8f10-8047f1791231","content":"In MSTest 3.x, you can inject `TestContext` via the constructor and combine `[TestInitialize]` for async setup. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext + synchronous init\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Sync setup here (runs per-test)\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Initialized async resources\");\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        _client?.Dispose();\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_client);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — receives `TestContext` via DI; use for sync setup (runs before `[TestInitialize]`)\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task`; use for async setup (runs per-test, after constructor)\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — for one-time class-level setup (must be `static`)\n- The old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern still works but constructor injection is preferred in MSTest 3.x","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f168856f-00a6-4c18-b50d-cb55ec7f65bc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), `TestContext` can be injected via constructor. Let me provide the recommended pattern for both sync and async initialization.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended approach is:\n1. Constructor injection for `TestContext` (instead of the old property-based approach)\n2. Use `[TestInitialize]` for per-test sync setup\n3. Use `[TestInitialize]` with `async Task` for per-test async setup\n4. Use `[ClassInitialize]` for one-time class setup\n\n\nNow I'll show the concrete implementation patterns they should use.","outputTokens":564,"requestId":"BD0B:2A497:1DF7166:21E8D3A:6A07CC7F"},"id":"298b0dc7-e761-47c3-b950-5a31c5dd3b7b","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:46:50.966Z","parentId":"d49b6815-feb6-4351-b3fa-7383683a9511"}
